CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 29, 1962, pg. 15, reads: "LOOK WHAT SANTA BROUGHT! - Little Tina [sic] Harris, daughter of Courier staff photographer Charles (Teenie) Harris, sits astride a rocking horse brought to her by Santa Claus. Droopy (lower left), another gift for her recent good behavior, watches the proceedings. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Tina Harris riding rocking horse in front of Christmas tree with "Miss Popularity" and "Fascination" games and pantograph in Harris home, 7604 Mulford Street, Homewood
